Use python 2.7 for the shperical harmonic transform module shtns
(https://users.isterre.fr/nschaeff/SHTns/)

https://conda.io/docs/user-guide/tasks/manage-environments.html#activate-env


for this:
conda create -n py27 python=2.7 anaconda

source activate py27   (now we are in a different environment with python 2.7)


conda install -c flomertens shtns
conda install netCDF4
conda install basemap





Sph-filter_polar-map.py - plots different spherical harmonic transforms on a polar map


Spherical_harmonics_filter.py in mother folder can be utilized in python 3.6